HEADWORD: Knuff
<hw>Knuff</hw> <pr>(n⟦ucr⟧f)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Gnof</er>
a churl.]</ety> <def>A lout; a clown.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The country <qex>knuffs</qex>, Hob, Dick, and Hick,⟦br⟧
